<h1>Problem 1740 - 2023 EMC, P2 of 4, G</h1>
<h2 class='difficulty'>Difficulty: 7</h2>
<p>Let \(ABC\) be a triangle such that \(\angle BAC = 90^\circ\). The incircle of triangle \(ABC\) is tangent to the sides \(\overline{BC}\), \(\overline{CA}\), \(\overline{AB}\) at \(D\), \(E\), \(F\) respectively. Let \(M\) be the midpoint of \(\overline{EF}\). Let \(P\) be the projection of \(A\) onto \(BC\) and \(K\) be the intersection of \(MP\) and \(AD\). Prove that the circumcircles of triangles \(AFE\) and \(PDK\) have equal radius.</p>
